\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\widctlpar\tx1440\tx2880\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\f1 
\par }\pard \ql \fi-1440\li1440\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1440\itap0 {\f1 
\par Author:\tab The author of this Mission Pack.
\par Title:\tab The title of the Mission Pack.
\par Description:\tab A colorful description of the mission.
\par URL:\tab A website related to this Mission Pack, often the author\rquote s home page.
\par SoloPlay:\tab Unused but reserved for future utilization.
\par CoopPlay:\tab Unused but reserved for future utilization.
\par BGColor1:\tab Red, green, and blue (RGB) values between 0 and 255 that define the background color used for the Mission Pack user interface screens.
\par BGColor2:\tab Unused but reserved for future utilization.
\par TextColor:\tab RGB color values used for some Mission Pack text.
\par BotProfile:\tab The filename of a file containing the roster of bot personalities to use with this Mission Pack.
\par }\pard\plain \s3\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs26\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\page The Easy.vdf, Normal.vdf, Hard.vdf, and Expert.vdf Files
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1 These files define the game structure.  E
ach file corresponds to the difficulty selected by the player.  In other words, if the player starts your mission with a difficulty of \'93normal\'94, the Normal.vdf file will be read.
\par 
\par It is highly recommended that you examine the CareerGame*.vdf files.  They contain the data for the standard CZ Counter-Terrorist Tour of Duty.
\par 
\par }\pard \ql \fi-1800\li1800\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1800\itap0 {\f1 InitialPoints:\tab The number of Reputation Points the player starts the game with.
\par MatchWins:\tab The minimum number of rounds a team must win in order to win a match.
\par MatchWinBy:\tab The number of wins a team must lead by in order to win a match.
\par Characters:\tab A space-separated list of bot names defining the roster of teammates that can be purchased with Reputation Points.  These bot names must have corresponding personality definitions in the bot database (ie: BotProfile.db).
\par CostAvailability:\tab Each teammate has a Reputation Point cost, from 1 to 5.  This section defines how many total Reputation Points the player must have to \'93unlock\'94 each cost level of teammate.  For example, a pair of numbers such as \'934\'94 and 
\'9315\'94 means that the player must have at least 15 Reputation Points to unlock cost 4 teammates.
\par Maps:\tab The set of maps used in this mission.  The name of each map section must match a bsp file located in czero\\maps, cstrike\\maps, or valve\\maps.  See the \'93Defining a Location (Maps)\'94 section for more information.\line  
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\page Defining a Location (Map)
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1 Maps are organized as \'93triplets\'94
, or sets of three maps. The first, second, and third maps form the first Tour of Duty, the fourth, fifth, and sixth are the second Tour of Duty, and so on.  All three maps in a Tour of Duty must be won in order to unlock the next Tour of Duty.
\par }\pard \ql \fi-1800\li1800\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1800\itap0 {\f1 
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx3600\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f28\fs20 \'93map name\'94
