\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f1 \'93map name\'94
\par The filename of the bsp to load for this location without the .bsp extension.  For example, \'93de_dust_cz\'94.
\par 
\par \'93bots\'94
\par This field is followed by a string containing a list of enemy bot names for this map.  Bots are added from left to right, in order.  For example, the list \'93Joe Fred Alex Barney\'94 would look up \'93Joe\'94
 in the missions bot database and add a bot with those parameters first, followed by \'93Fred\'94, \'93Alex\'94, and \'93Barney\'94 up to the desired number of enemies for that location.
\par 
\par \'93minEnemies\'94
\par This value defines the minimum number of enemies the player will face on this map.
\par 
\par \'93threshold\'94
\par This number defines the Reputation Point value above which one enemy is added for every additional Reputation Point until we run out of bots on the \'93bots\'94 line.
\par 
\par \'93tasks\'94
\par This field defines a list of tasks/challenges the player must complete to win this map.  Each task, and that task\rquote s parameters, must be enclosed within single quotes within the overall string.  For example:
\par 
\par         "tasks"       " 'kill 7' 'kill 2 survive' 'winfast 60' "
\par 
\par For a full list of tasks, see the Task Reference section.
\par     
\par \page \'93FriendlyFire\'94
\par If this is set to zero, friends cannot be hurt by each others weapons.  If \'93FriendlyFire\'94 is \'931\'94, friends can hurt each other.
\par 
\par \'93commands\'94
\par The \'93<console command string>\'94 is sent to the console when the map is loaded.  This can be used to change system parameters just as if the user had entered the string in the console.  Note that certain commands (ie: mp_startmoney) don\rquote 
t function, as they are reset by the system after these commands have been given.
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\i\f1\fs28\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\page Task Reference
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f1 
For each task listed below, required parameters are enclosed in < >, and optional parameters are enclosed in [ ].  Multiple optional parameters are separated by a vertical bar.
\par 
\par The optional parameter \'93survive\'94 means the player must complete the task in a single round without being killed.  The optional parameter \'93inarow\'94 means the player must complete the task over potentially several rounds without dying.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\ul General Tasks
